node.title: Victorian daily COVID cases dip below 1,000 for the first time in weeks
node.alt: Social distancing signage is seen along St Kilda beach.
node.description: Victoria records 989 new local COVID-19 cases and nine deaths, the first time daily case numbers have been below 1,000 since September 28.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 989\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and nine\u00a0deaths, the first time daily case numbers have been below 1,000 since September 28.", "There are now 19,409\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 318\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "The new cases were identified from 48,002\u00a0test results reported yesterday.", "There were 16,158\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "There are now 667\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 127\u00a0are in intensive care and 76\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "
New tier 1 exposure sites in Victoria
", "Health authorities have added new tier 1 venues to Victoria's public list of COVID-19 exposure sites.", "The new tier 1 venues are:", "Anyone who has been to a tier 1 exposure site at the specified time\u00a0must get tested and isolate for 14 days if unvaccinated, or for seven days if fully vaccinated.", "Check the list below for all of the exposure sites and times.", "You can find information on testing site hours and your\u00a0nearest site on the Department of Health\u00a0website.", "", "
